  "full_text_flowing_modernisation_text_block": "Based on the honorable occurrence of the auspicious accession of His Majesty the King of Kings as described above,\nin the pulpits of the noble mosques located throughout all the Imperial Well-Protected Domains,\nit has become necessary for the exalted sermon to be read in the illustrious name of His Excellency the World Guardian;\ntherefore, concerning this and regarding other commandments and admonitions of Royal correctness,\naddressed separately to all the illustrious officials and servants located in Anatolia and Rumelia,\nthe justice-bearing orders of His Imperial Majesty, which have been issued, [reflect] the perfection of the mercy and compassion of\nHis Imperial Majesty; arising from this, [to ensure] the inhabitants and the poor are spared from such things as giving service and money,\nand with his sublime desire for their protection from burden and trouble, the appointment of [special] agents has been dispensed with,\nand [the orders] have been sent for delivery solely via couriers; and a customary writing containing the announcement of the Grand Vizierate\nwhich has been drafted, along with the Viceregal missives of high import, [are to be given] to the governors, mutasarrifs, and other officials'\nrepresentatives and directors of affairs who are present here [in the capital], and through their mediation\nand knowledge they are to be sent; and that for these matters not a single coin nor a grain should be taken from the poor,\nthis particular point has been emphatically warned; and also to the inhabitants of the Sublime Abode of the Sultanate [Istanbul], in every case,\nregarding the execution of Divine commands and the duty of acquiring the Creator's approval, once again\nthe necessary Sharia-compliant warnings containing instructions to pay care and attention to their perfection have been carried out;\ntherefore, for the sake of reminder, it has been declared and notified in this place as well.\nThe former Director of Imperial Buildings, Abdülhalim Efendi, has by necessity been appointed again to the aforesaid directorship,\nand the other Abdülhalim Efendi, who was in the aforesaid service, has been assigned to the Hüdavendigar [Bursa]\nParadise-dwelling Majesty's exalted tomb construction and arrangement duty;\nthese matters having been approved and decreed, the two aforesaid individuals, on the twentieth\nsecond day of the aforesaid month, a Thursday, were summoned to the Sublime Porte, and their duties were executed and announced\naccordingly.\nAPPOINTMENTS OF THE ILMIYE [LEARNED CLASS]\nBy the prosperity-increasing manifestation and issuance of the benevolence-showing Imperial Command,\nand in accordance with the sublime requirement of the noble decree pledged to high meaning of His Majesty the King of Kings:\nThe judgeship of Mecca the Honored—may God Exalted honor it until the Last Day—is to be held from the first of Muharrem of the coming year,\nand its respected rank is to be considered valid from the day of appointment;\n[this has been granted to] the former Judge of Jerusalem the Noble, the grandson of Hatvanizade, es-Seyyid Yahya Tevfik\nEfendi. Likewise, the judgeship of Medina the Illuminated—may it endure with eternal happiness—\nis to be held from the aforesaid first day [of Muharrem], with its rank valid from the day of appointment,\n[and has been granted to] Ahmed Efendi of Afyonkarahisar. On this Tuesday, the twentieth of Rabi' al-Thani,\nby the high sign of His Excellency the Refuge of Fatwas [Sheikh ul-Islam], these appointments and favors were granted, and separate sublime orders\nwere issued, thereby gladdening the two aforesaid individuals.",
  "summary": "This document from the Takvîm-i Vekâyi (July 1839) outlines administrative and religious appointments following the accession of the new Sultan (Abdülmecid I). It mandates that the Friday sermon (hutbe) be read in the new Sultan's name across all imperial domains. To spare the populace from financial burden, the dispatch of special agents is cancelled; instead, orders are sent via couriers to local officials through their representatives in Istanbul, with strict warnings against extracting money from the poor. Administratively, Abdülhalim Efendi is reinstated as Director of Imperial Buildings, while another Abdülhalim Efendi is assigned to oversee the construction of the late Sultan's tomb in Bursa. In the Ilmiye (religious) class, es-Seyyid Yahya Tevfik is appointed Judge of Mecca, and Ahmed Efendi is appointed Judge of Medina, effective from the coming Muharrem."
